cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

Reasoning: The paper deals with domain adaptation in computer vision, specifically with tensor representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a learning-based method, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of tensor representations also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a joint optimization problem, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
